Video 1 — Introduction to Python

Overview:
Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language. It emphasizes readability, simplicity, and rapid development. Supports multiple paradigms: procedural, OOP, functional. Widely used in AI, data science, automation, and web development.

Key Concepts:

Dynamic typing, automatic memory management
Extensive standard library
Cross-platform support

Example:

print("Hello, Python!")

Practical Insights:

Ideal for rapid prototyping
Focus on clear, readable code to reduce bugs
Foundation for AI, ML, and automation projects
